name it vestigia
add commands like:
>vestigia trace -f firefox  -- to find all files that were installed while installing firefox
>vestigia purge (or even exorcist) firefox  -- to delete firefox and delete all files, logs, etc that came with it
if a file has more than one source tag, just delete the tag

use words like persistent data (for files, metadate, cache, etc) and upstream operations (for pacman operations)

make a readme
